            "last_activity_date": 1278632747,
            "creation_date": 1278630723,
            "body": "<p>If you want to run in java 1.5 then you <em>should<\/em> compile in java 1.5 or lower.  <\/p>\n\n<p>Alternatively, if you simply must run JDK 6 then as @Paul Tomblin suggests you can use the -target javac option.  One warning on this though, if you are using any of the new Java 1.6 API features javac 1.6 (e.g. <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/docs/cd/E17409_01/javase/6/docs/api/java/io/File.html#setWritable%28boolean%29\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">setting File perms<\/a>) javac will not complain but you will get errors when running this code in java 1.5.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 3208706,
            "question_id": 3208693,
            "last_edit_date": 1278632747
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/99660662e89949a4b53cd97bc199ead1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2397,
                "user_type": "registered",
